1
00:01:01,880 --> 00:01:02,800
Miss Haitang.

2
00:01:03,160 --> 00:01:04,200
Zhou Shiqing.

3
00:01:04,920 --> 00:01:05,920
Zhou Shiqing.

4
00:01:06,640 --> 00:01:07,320
Haitang,

5
00:01:07,760 --> 00:01:08,690
why are you here?

6
00:01:08,840 --> 00:01:10,300
My apartment got flooded.

7
00:01:10,360 --> 00:01:12,160
I came to stay here for the night.

8
00:01:14,440 --> 00:01:16,900
Does Haitang come to the Zhou Mansion often?

9
00:01:17,120 --> 00:01:18,640
Whenever Madam isn't home,

10
00:01:18,640 --> 00:01:20,960
Master would send someone to pick Haitang up.

11
00:01:20,960 --> 00:01:23,320
But this Haitang has quite a personality.

12
00:01:23,680 --> 00:01:25,940
Nine times out of ten, she wouldn't come.

13
00:01:26,080 --> 00:01:27,000
Every time,

14
00:01:27,720 --> 00:01:30,840
Master has to beg her in all sorts of ways before she agrees.

15
00:01:30,840 --> 00:01:31,970
What happened then?

16
00:01:32,400 --> 00:01:33,200
Then,

17
00:01:33,360 --> 00:01:34,560
not long after,

18
00:01:35,080 --> 00:01:37,410
Master came out of the room calling for me.

19
00:01:37,800 --> 00:01:39,200
He asked me to arrange a rickshaw

20
00:01:39,200 --> 00:01:40,520
to take her to a hotel,

21
00:01:40,800 --> 00:01:42,960
and even booked a room for her for three days.

22
00:01:42,960 --> 00:01:44,840
Do you remember when she arrived?

23
00:01:46,720 --> 00:01:48,600
Around two in the morning.

24
00:01:49,640 --> 00:01:51,560
Which hotel did Haitang stay at,

25
00:01:51,680 --> 00:01:52,680
do you remember?

26
00:01:54,440 --> 00:01:55,240
Chinese City,

27
00:01:56,200 --> 00:01:57,600
Taifeng Hotel.

28
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:07,400
Didn't she book the room for three days?

29
00:02:07,400 --> 00:02:08,560
Where is she?

30
00:02:12,960 --> 00:02:15,000
There are no signs of anyone living here.

31
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:15,800
It looks like

32
00:02:15,840 --> 00:02:17,800
Haitang never stayed here at all.

33
00:02:18,600 --> 00:02:21,000
Could she have gone to someone else's home?

34
00:02:23,240 --> 00:02:26,560
This hotel is considered decent in the Chinese area.

35
00:02:27,079 --> 00:02:29,120
Booking a room late at night and not staying

36
00:02:29,120 --> 00:02:30,250
doesn't make sense.

37
00:02:30,840 --> 00:02:32,000
You mean,

38
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:34,320
she made up an excuse

39
00:02:34,440 --> 00:02:35,920
to go to Comprador Zhou's house?

40
00:02:35,920 --> 00:02:38,480
Do you remember the butler telling us

41
00:02:38,560 --> 00:02:40,420
he heard Haitang taking a shower?

42
00:02:40,920 --> 00:02:41,560
And we...

43
00:02:42,120 --> 00:02:44,160
coincidentally, in the bathroom drain,

44
00:02:44,160 --> 00:02:46,690
found He Xiaolian's blood and cotton thread.

45
00:02:46,960 --> 00:02:49,020
Isn't that too much of a coincidence?

46
00:02:49,040 --> 00:02:50,240
You suspect

47
00:02:50,800 --> 00:02:52,920
the blood and cotton thread at his house

48
00:02:52,920 --> 00:02:55,180
were placed there by Haitang on purpose?

49
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:58,760
How did she know about He Xiaolian?

50
00:02:58,760 --> 00:03:00,680
Didn't we test that bloodstain?

51
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:03,460
It matches He Xiaolian's blood type.

52
00:03:04,920 --> 00:03:07,120
Where did she get He Xiaolian's blood?

53
00:03:08,640 --> 00:03:09,400
Look.

54
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:12,880
The victim really died in Comprador Zhou's house.

55
00:03:13,080 --> 00:03:14,360
Then how did she move the body

56
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:17,360
from the Chinese territory to the French Concession?

57
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:24,400
This lady

58
00:03:24,400 --> 00:03:25,960
looks a bit unfamiliar.

59
00:03:26,320 --> 00:03:27,650
I didn't really notice.

60
00:03:30,480 --> 00:03:32,079
I have seen this lady before.

61
00:03:32,440 --> 00:03:34,760
She was in a rickshaw the night before last.

62
00:03:34,760 --> 00:03:36,360
She seemed very ill.

63
00:03:37,079 --> 00:03:38,810
Didn't you check it carefully?

64
00:03:39,040 --> 00:03:40,000
We did.

65
00:03:40,240 --> 00:03:42,240
There was nothing wrong with the rickshaw.

66
00:03:42,240 --> 00:03:43,680
But the rickshaw puller said

67
00:03:43,680 --> 00:03:44,680
he had to rush her to a hospital

68
00:03:44,680 --> 00:03:46,140
in the French Concession.

69
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:49,079
She looked deathly pale

70
00:03:49,079 --> 00:03:50,340
and barely conscious.

71
00:03:50,680 --> 00:03:51,720
It was a matter of life and death,

72
00:03:51,720 --> 00:03:52,880
so I let them pass.

73
00:04:36,640 --> 00:04:37,600
Who is it?

74
00:04:38,800 --> 00:04:39,960
I live upstairs.

75
00:04:40,080 --> 00:04:41,360
I have a water leak.

76
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:47,280
Who are you?

77
00:04:47,840 --> 00:04:49,040
We're from the Central Police Station.

78
00:04:49,040 --> 00:04:50,640
We need to ask you a few questions.

79
00:04:50,640 --> 00:04:51,520
I don't have time.

80
00:04:51,520 --> 00:04:53,780
I have to go to work at the Grand Shanghai.

81
00:04:55,960 --> 00:04:57,480
Didn't you call in sick?

82
00:04:58,440 --> 00:04:59,240
So what?

83
00:04:59,640 --> 00:05:02,000
Are you in charge of sick leave now?

84
00:05:02,360 --> 00:05:03,600
Zhou Shiqing, Comprador Zhou.

85
00:05:03,600 --> 00:05:04,460
Do you know him?

86
00:05:08,480 --> 00:05:10,880
When was the last time you saw Zhou Shiqing?

87
00:05:12,040 --> 00:05:13,300
The night before last.

88
00:05:13,560 --> 00:05:14,280
Why?

89
00:05:14,520 --> 00:05:15,650
Tell me the details.

90
00:05:17,200 --> 00:05:19,760
There was a water leak in my room that night.

91
00:05:20,240 --> 00:05:22,770
So I wanted to crash at his place for the night.

92
00:05:23,240 --> 00:05:24,680
But I don't know what got into him.

93
00:05:24,680 --> 00:05:26,200
He kicked me out.

94
00:05:26,880 --> 00:05:28,740
Then he booked a hotel room for me.

95
00:05:30,360 --> 00:05:32,420
But you never actually stayed there.

96
00:05:32,440 --> 00:05:34,159
That room faces the street.

97
00:05:34,360 --> 00:05:35,400
It's too noisy.

98
00:05:36,120 --> 00:05:38,880
But you inspectors are quite interesting.

99
00:05:39,040 --> 00:05:40,159
You know everything,

100
00:05:40,159 --> 00:05:41,159
yet you still ask.

101
00:05:43,159 --> 00:05:44,360
Zhou Shiqing is dead.

102
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:46,000
Did you know that?

103
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:49,040
Is he dead?

104
00:05:49,800 --> 00:05:52,530
He was alive and kicking just a couple of days ago.

105
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:54,400
But it's not surprising.

106
00:05:54,640 --> 00:05:55,960
For someone like him,

107
00:05:55,960 --> 00:05:58,090
he looked respectable on the surface,

108
00:05:58,120 --> 00:05:59,800
but who knows what dirty deeds

109
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:00,960
he did in secret?

110
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:04,960
From the sound of it,

111
00:06:05,520 --> 00:06:06,980
you had a problem with him.

112
00:06:07,880 --> 00:06:10,240
I was just playing along with him.

113
00:06:10,240 --> 00:06:12,000
We were just using each other.

114
00:06:12,880 --> 00:06:15,360
You wouldn't suspect me

115
00:06:15,360 --> 00:06:17,620
just because I had a past with him, right?

116
00:06:18,080 --> 00:06:20,520
He's been with plenty of girls.

117
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:22,370
Enough to keep you busy.

118
00:06:23,480 --> 00:06:24,010
Perfect.

119
00:06:24,640 --> 00:06:25,700
Help us take a look.

120
00:06:26,120 --> 00:06:27,360
Among these girls,

121
00:06:27,640 --> 00:06:29,840
who has been to Comprador Zhou's house?

122
00:06:31,720 --> 00:06:32,720
I don't know them.

123
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:35,880
He wouldn't let me see him bringing someone home.

124
00:06:35,880 --> 00:06:36,880
She has a point.

125
00:06:37,560 --> 00:06:39,120
How many times have I told you?

126
00:06:39,120 --> 00:06:40,360
Zhou Shiqing isn't stupid.

127
00:06:40,360 --> 00:06:42,620
How could he let them run into each other?

128
00:06:43,280 --> 00:06:44,409
Sorry to bother you.

129
00:06:46,920 --> 00:06:48,440
Why are you still keeping this?

130
00:06:48,440 --> 00:06:49,480
With the way you investigate,

131
00:06:49,480 --> 00:06:50,940
the criminal is long gone.

132
00:06:52,360 --> 00:06:53,240
I really wonder now

133
00:06:53,240 --> 00:06:54,840
how you became an officer.

134
00:06:56,440 --> 00:06:57,120
Let's go.

135
00:07:09,240 --> 00:07:10,200
Found it.

136
00:07:16,880 --> 00:07:20,480
It seems Haitang and He Xiaolian were more than just acquaintances.

137
00:07:20,480 --> 00:07:22,120
So their identities as a student and a showgirl

138
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:23,120
were just a cover

139
00:07:23,520 --> 00:07:25,380
to facilitate drug trafficking.

140
00:07:54,480 --> 00:07:55,720
It seems she and He Xiaolian

141
00:07:55,720 --> 00:07:57,480
were not just drug trafficking partners.

142
00:07:57,480 --> 00:07:58,760
They were actually quite close.

143
00:07:58,760 --> 00:08:01,220
She dug up the body and framed Comprador Zhou

144
00:08:01,560 --> 00:08:03,200
just to avenge He Xiaolian.

145
00:08:03,200 --> 00:08:04,400
But when He Xiaolian left

146
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:06,200
Comprador Zhou's house, she was still alive.

147
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:08,320
But the symptoms the sentry described

148
00:08:08,320 --> 00:08:09,800
sound like opium poisoning.

149
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:11,320
It must have been at Comprador Zhou's house

150
00:08:11,320 --> 00:08:13,440
that the fish intestine inside He Xiaolian ruptured,

151
00:08:13,440 --> 00:08:15,570
causing an acute poisoning reaction.

152
00:08:17,240 --> 00:08:18,120
Curly hair,

153
00:08:18,600 --> 00:08:19,930
and an injury on her arm.

154
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:22,040
She definitely killed Comprador Zhou.

155
00:08:22,040 --> 00:08:23,000
Then what are we waiting for?

156
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:24,120
Take her to the police station.

157
00:08:24,120 --> 00:08:24,640
Wait.

158
00:08:25,840 --> 00:08:27,800
The butler said Haitang left at 2 AM

159
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:29,400
for Comprador Zhou's house.

160
00:08:29,400 --> 00:08:31,280
Around 2 AM.

161
00:08:31,920 --> 00:08:33,400
And the person who entered Baogong Workshop

162
00:08:33,400 --> 00:08:34,659
also went there at 2 AM.

163
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:36,320
Around 2 AM.

164
00:08:36,679 --> 00:08:38,799
The Zhou Mansion isn't close to Baogong Workshop.

165
00:08:38,799 --> 00:08:40,159
She must have an accomplice.

166
00:08:40,159 --> 00:08:41,280
Now that we're here,

167
00:08:41,280 --> 00:08:42,799
she'll definitely go tip off

168
00:08:42,799 --> 00:08:43,799
the other person.

169
00:08:44,960 --> 00:08:45,440
Bao.

170
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:47,000
Find a few strays

171
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:49,530
to keep an eye on Haitang near this apartment.

172
00:09:25,480 --> 00:09:26,600
Business is so slow.

173
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:28,840
Yeah, I only had one fare all day.

174
00:09:36,320 --> 00:09:37,380
I found the fabric.

175
00:09:38,120 --> 00:09:40,800
I had the boys visit over twenty tailor shops.

176
00:09:41,160 --> 00:09:43,320
Finally, at a place called Ruixiang Tailor Shop,

177
00:09:43,320 --> 00:09:44,440
we found the material.

178
00:09:44,440 --> 00:09:46,900
This material is custom-made by their shop.

179
00:09:46,920 --> 00:09:47,840
It's very rare.

180
00:09:48,080 --> 00:09:48,960
But six months ago,

181
00:09:48,960 --> 00:09:49,560
someone

182
00:09:49,560 --> 00:09:51,440
ordered a full outfit here.

183
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:52,360
Three months ago,

184
00:09:52,360 --> 00:09:53,760
the outfit was picked up.

185
00:09:53,920 --> 00:09:55,440
It was the owner of Kangren Noodle Shop,

186
00:09:55,440 --> 00:09:56,200
Zhang Jinxi.

187
00:10:00,440 --> 00:10:03,200
Could Haitang's accomplice be Zhang Jinxi?

188
00:10:04,360 --> 00:10:05,920
But he's too old.

189
00:10:06,120 --> 00:10:07,200
What does age have to do with it?

190
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:09,530
Being old doesn't mean he's in poor shape.

191
00:10:15,480 --> 00:10:16,940
Why is there so much smoke?

192
00:10:22,680 --> 00:10:24,120
So much smoke.

193
00:10:24,120 --> 00:10:25,120
Is there a fire?

194
00:10:42,120 --> 00:10:43,920
Cuckoo.

195
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:47,930
Let's wait a bit longer.

196
00:10:48,360 --> 00:10:49,820
They have their eyes on me.

197
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:51,520
You need to be careful too.

198
00:10:51,520 --> 00:10:52,580
Do you understand?

199
00:10:53,200 --> 00:10:55,000
I will come find you again later.

200
00:10:55,040 --> 00:10:55,680
Okay?

201
00:11:02,040 --> 00:11:04,000
I made that clear ages ago.

202
00:11:04,120 --> 00:11:05,440
The fabric Mr. Zhang used

203
00:11:05,440 --> 00:11:07,000
for your thin cotton shirt last time

204
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:07,920
had a problem.

205
00:11:08,240 --> 00:11:09,560
I am terribly sorry.

206
00:11:10,120 --> 00:11:11,800
We will make you a new one.

207
00:11:11,880 --> 00:11:12,680
Young man,

208
00:11:13,480 --> 00:11:14,160
but

209
00:11:14,400 --> 00:11:16,240
the shirt I bought

210
00:11:16,600 --> 00:11:17,660
is perfectly fine.

211
00:11:18,200 --> 00:11:18,860
Why don't we

212
00:11:18,960 --> 00:11:20,000
just let it go?

213
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:21,440
That won't do.

214
00:11:21,440 --> 00:11:22,440
Our boss said

215
00:11:22,440 --> 00:11:23,680
we can't be like those shysters

216
00:11:23,680 --> 00:11:25,520
at Hongxing House across the street.

217
00:11:25,520 --> 00:11:27,320
They used scraps as good fabric,

218
00:11:27,720 --> 00:11:29,400
thinking they could get away with it.

219
00:11:29,400 --> 00:11:30,200
Last month,

220
00:11:30,320 --> 00:11:31,760
their signboard was torn down.

221
00:11:31,760 --> 00:11:34,360
Now they're stuck darning socks on the street.

222
00:11:35,120 --> 00:11:36,240
Our Ruixiang,

223
00:11:36,240 --> 00:11:37,680
this time-honored brand,

224
00:11:37,680 --> 00:11:39,120
was built by the old shopkeeper

225
00:11:39,120 --> 00:11:40,480
with thirty years of stitching.

226
00:11:40,480 --> 00:11:42,040
If the neighbors start

227
00:11:42,360 --> 00:11:43,720
cursing us behind our backs,

228
00:11:43,720 --> 00:11:45,980
I, Wang Amao, will be the first to object.

229
00:11:46,280 --> 00:11:47,280
Yes, yes.

230
00:11:47,440 --> 00:11:48,840
Wait here for a moment.

231
00:11:48,840 --> 00:11:50,100
I'll get it for you now.

232
00:11:55,680 --> 00:11:56,320
This is it.

233
00:11:56,720 --> 00:11:57,680
Is it this one?

234
00:11:59,560 --> 00:12:01,400
My boss was right.

235
00:12:01,560 --> 00:12:03,360
It has a huge hole eaten by moths.

236
00:12:05,160 --> 00:12:06,480
It's possible that

237
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:08,400
my grandson Shisan

238
00:12:08,440 --> 00:12:09,840
accidentally ruined it.

239
00:12:10,120 --> 00:12:11,120
So this garment

240
00:12:11,480 --> 00:12:12,680
isn't for you to wear?

241
00:12:13,840 --> 00:12:17,000
It's a birthday gift I bought for my grandson.

242
00:12:19,560 --> 00:12:20,220
Boss Zhang.

243
00:12:20,400 --> 00:12:21,660
Where is Zhang Shisan?

244
00:12:22,920 --> 00:12:23,780
Inspector Lin.

245
00:12:23,880 --> 00:12:24,940
What is this about?

246
00:12:29,320 --> 00:12:30,160
Shisan!

247
00:12:31,560 --> 00:12:32,560
Shisan!

248
00:12:34,440 --> 00:12:35,080
Shisan!

249
00:12:45,200 --> 00:12:46,260
He hasn't gone far.

250
00:12:47,400 --> 00:12:48,320
Block all the intersections.

251
00:12:48,320 --> 00:12:49,320
Bring him back.

252
00:12:49,400 --> 00:12:49,930
Yes, sir.

253
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:22,560
Lin Lan.

254
00:13:36,840 --> 00:13:37,840
To your knowledge,

255
00:13:37,840 --> 00:13:38,760
does Zhang Shisan know

256
00:13:38,760 --> 00:13:40,420
a dancing girl named Haitang?

257
00:13:42,600 --> 00:13:44,000
My grandson Shisan

258
00:13:44,280 --> 00:13:45,160
rarely goes out

259
00:13:45,640 --> 00:13:46,770
and has few friends.

260
00:13:47,080 --> 00:13:48,880
How could he know any women?

261
00:13:49,760 --> 00:13:50,480
In that case,

262
00:13:50,480 --> 00:13:52,000
if there is any news about Zhang Shisan,

263
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:53,330
notify us immediately.

264
00:14:00,080 --> 00:14:00,640
Bad news.

265
00:14:00,960 --> 00:14:02,040
Haitang is missing.

266
00:14:02,040 --> 00:14:03,000
We searched her room.

267
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:03,840
Her luggage is gone.

268
00:14:03,840 --> 00:14:05,840
We don't know when she slipped away.

269
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:13,720
We suspect

270
00:14:13,920 --> 00:14:15,400
that Haitang and He Xiaolian

271
00:14:15,400 --> 00:14:18,460
are smuggling opium for the seller using their bodies.

272
00:14:18,800 --> 00:14:20,240
Not only do they know each other,

273
00:14:20,240 --> 00:14:21,880
but they are also close.

274
00:14:23,200 --> 00:14:24,280
After He Xiaolian was killed,

275
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:25,840
Haitang and Zhang Shisan

276
00:14:25,840 --> 00:14:27,440
dug up her body

277
00:14:27,720 --> 00:14:30,120
and swapped it with Comprador Zhou's gift.

278
00:14:30,920 --> 00:14:32,200
Bring them back.

279
00:14:32,720 --> 00:14:33,840
I'll interrogate them myself.

280
00:14:33,840 --> 00:14:34,640
No, well...

281
00:14:34,640 --> 00:14:35,360
I can't.

282
00:14:36,200 --> 00:14:37,320
They're missing.

283
00:14:40,760 --> 00:14:41,680
What the hell?

284
00:14:42,040 --> 00:14:43,840
You're telling me they ran away?

285
00:14:46,080 --> 00:14:47,080
I was thinking...

286
00:14:47,320 --> 00:14:49,440
Even if we found out

287
00:14:49,600 --> 00:14:52,130
that they moved He Xiaolian's body together,

288
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:53,800
the two of them

289
00:14:53,800 --> 00:14:56,330
wouldn't necessarily have to flee together.

290
00:14:56,560 --> 00:14:57,640
Unless...

291
00:14:58,120 --> 00:14:59,920
when Comprador Zhou was killed,

292
00:15:00,320 --> 00:15:02,720
besides Haitang,

293
00:15:03,200 --> 00:15:05,400
Zhang Shisan might have been there too.

294
00:15:05,600 --> 00:15:06,120
Right.

295
00:15:06,720 --> 00:15:08,320
Haitang is a woman, after all.

296
00:15:08,320 --> 00:15:10,120
It wouldn't be easy for her to kill Comprador Zhou.

297
00:15:10,120 --> 00:15:11,320
If Zhang Shisan was there,

298
00:15:11,320 --> 00:15:12,380
it all makes sense.

299
00:15:12,960 --> 00:15:15,620
I've been to that noodle shop a few times before,

300
00:15:15,760 --> 00:15:18,520
and I've dealt with Zhang Shisan.

301
00:15:21,200 --> 00:15:21,960
No.

302
00:15:22,320 --> 00:15:23,160
I'm not close enough to him

303
00:15:23,160 --> 00:15:24,760
to know where he is right now.

304
00:15:26,120 --> 00:15:27,080
Come to think of it,

305
00:15:27,080 --> 00:15:29,940
that kid really is different from ordinary people.

306
00:15:41,960 --> 00:15:43,560
How did this open?

307
00:15:46,760 --> 00:15:47,960
There, it's closed.

308
00:15:54,760 --> 00:15:55,220
Shisan.

309
00:15:56,040 --> 00:15:57,240
Didn't I tell you to go back?

310
00:15:57,240 --> 00:15:58,120
Why are you still here?

311
00:15:58,120 --> 00:15:59,200
I...

312
00:16:01,400 --> 00:16:02,460
don't know the way.

313
00:16:03,840 --> 00:16:06,760
You mean Zhang Shisan

314
00:16:07,320 --> 00:16:09,240
has never ridden in a car,

315
00:16:09,240 --> 00:16:11,170
and doesn't even know the way back?

316
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:12,760
At the time,

317
00:16:12,880 --> 00:16:14,120
I thought the kid

318
00:16:14,120 --> 00:16:15,240
was kept on a tight leash

319
00:16:15,240 --> 00:16:16,370
and rarely went out.

320
00:16:17,360 --> 00:16:19,760
I didn't expect it to be related to a murder.

321
00:16:22,040 --> 00:16:23,970
No matter how strict his family is,

322
00:16:24,160 --> 00:16:25,820
it shouldn't be this extreme.

323
00:16:26,720 --> 00:16:27,250
Exactly.

324
00:16:28,160 --> 00:16:29,890
How could a normal grandfather

325
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:32,000
let his grandson turn out like this?

326
00:16:35,000 --> 00:16:36,440
Uncle, you're here.

327
00:16:36,960 --> 00:16:38,000
I'm here, Shisan.

328
00:16:40,680 --> 00:16:42,940
They were all caught fresh this morning.

329
00:16:51,960 --> 00:16:53,880
Crabs for sale!

330
00:16:54,080 --> 00:16:55,440
Brother, buy two crabs.

331
00:16:56,320 --> 00:16:57,440
Take a look.

332
00:16:57,440 --> 00:16:58,560
Freshwater crabs. Our Taihu crabs.

333
00:16:58,560 --> 00:16:59,360
Full of golden roe.

334
00:16:59,360 --> 00:17:00,880
The fuzz is snowy white.

335
00:17:00,880 --> 00:17:01,920
Our Taihu crabs.

336
00:17:01,920 --> 00:17:02,720
Full of golden roe.

337
00:17:02,720 --> 00:17:04,640
Look at her crabs' legs.

338
00:17:04,960 --> 00:17:06,290
As thin as matchsticks.

339
00:17:06,440 --> 00:17:07,839
Only yours are good, huh?

340
00:17:07,960 --> 00:17:08,560
Of course.

341
00:17:08,720 --> 00:17:09,200
Only yours are good?

342
00:17:09,200 --> 00:17:09,680
Only mine are good.

343
00:17:09,680 --> 00:17:10,810
What are you saying?

344
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:11,599
Stop arguing.

345
00:17:11,599 --> 00:17:12,400
Stop arguing.

346
00:17:13,440 --> 00:17:15,480
Look closely, I'm from the Central Police Station.

347
00:17:15,480 --> 00:17:16,599
I need to ask you something.

348
00:17:16,599 --> 00:17:19,040
Do you supply crabs to Kangren Noodle Restaurant?

349
00:17:19,040 --> 00:17:19,680
My shop supplies them.

350
00:17:19,680 --> 00:17:20,480
It's my shop. It's mine.

351
00:17:20,480 --> 00:17:21,079
Mine.

352
00:17:21,400 --> 00:17:22,520
My shop delivers them.

353
00:17:22,520 --> 00:17:23,280
They are ours.

354
00:17:23,280 --> 00:17:23,920
My shop delivers them.

355
00:17:23,920 --> 00:17:24,920
You're talking nonsense.

356
00:17:24,920 --> 00:17:25,839
Our family...

357
00:17:29,520 --> 00:17:30,520
I never expected this.

358
00:17:30,520 --> 00:17:32,720
How could Shisan do something like this?

359
00:17:32,720 --> 00:17:34,960
He usually seems so well-behaved.

360
00:17:35,040 --> 00:17:36,080
Think carefully.

361
00:17:36,720 --> 00:17:38,380
Where else could he have gone?

362
00:17:41,560 --> 00:17:42,220
Sir, Ma'am,

363
00:17:42,400 --> 00:17:44,460
when did you first meet Zhang Shisan?

364
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:46,440
About ten years ago.

365
00:17:47,120 --> 00:17:48,960
Once when I went to deliver crabs,

366
00:17:48,960 --> 00:17:51,220
Mr. Zhang was with a boy of seven or eight.

367
00:17:51,320 --> 00:17:52,440
Mr. Zhang told us

368
00:17:52,960 --> 00:17:55,490
his son and daughter-in-law had an accident,

369
00:17:55,760 --> 00:17:57,760
leaving behind only this grandson,

370
00:17:57,880 --> 00:17:58,680
Zhang Shisan.

371
00:17:59,360 --> 00:18:01,690
Do you remember anything about the child,

372
00:18:01,840 --> 00:18:03,440
or notice anything special?

373
00:18:03,480 --> 00:18:04,120
The kid...

374
00:18:04,720 --> 00:18:05,920
was nice.

375
00:18:06,360 --> 00:18:07,760
He had a rosy complexion.

376
00:18:08,400 --> 00:18:09,400
It's a pity, though.

377
00:18:09,400 --> 00:18:10,530
He had a disability.

378
00:18:10,760 --> 00:18:11,560
A disability?

379
00:18:12,120 --> 00:18:15,560
Part of his right pinky finger was missing.

380
00:18:18,600 --> 00:18:19,560
Detectives,

381
00:18:19,680 --> 00:18:21,320
don't listen to her nonsense.

382
00:18:21,320 --> 00:18:22,320
Kangren Noodle Shop,

383
00:18:22,320 --> 00:18:23,280
five years ago,

384
00:18:23,280 --> 00:18:24,680
stopped buying her crabs

385
00:18:24,680 --> 00:18:25,740
and switched to me.

386
00:18:26,200 --> 00:18:28,520
She's just jealous and talking nonsense.

387
00:18:28,520 --> 00:18:29,320
You're lying.

388
00:18:31,800 --> 00:18:32,730
What do you mean?

389
00:18:34,360 --> 00:18:36,040
Ever since I met Thirteen,

390
00:18:36,400 --> 00:18:38,560
his fingers have been fine.

391
00:18:38,960 --> 00:18:40,620
Later, when Thirteen grew up,

392
00:18:40,920 --> 00:18:43,760
he still bought stock from me every now and then.

393
00:18:44,320 --> 00:18:45,120
Even now,

394
00:18:45,560 --> 00:18:47,760
his fingers are perfectly fine.
